  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SocialMedia</code> class represents a social media platform. It stores exactly four users and has space to hold up to two public posts and two private posts.\r\n\r\nThe <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">User</code> class represents a user on a social media platform. It has instance variables for the user's <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">username</code> and the privacy status of their profile. If <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">isPrivate</code> is <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">true</code>, their profile is private.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #1:</strong> Write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">private</code> method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">markPost()</code> in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SocialMedia</code> class to return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> with the post containing the user's <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">username</code>. If their profile is private, the post should begin with <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"[PRIVATE] \"</code>.\r\n\r\n- For example, if <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">new User(\"sunnydays\", false)</code> creates the post <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"Loving the sunshine!\"</code>, the method should return:  \r\n  <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">sunnydays: Loving the sunshine!</code>  \r\n- If <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">new User(\"nightowl42\", true)</code> creates the same post, the method should return:  \r\n  <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">[PRIVATE] nightowl42: Loving the sunshine!</code>\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #2:</strong> Write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">createPost()</code> method in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SocialMedia</code> class to:\r\n- Use the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">markPost()</code> method to format the post.\r\n- Store the result in the first available public or private post slot (there are two of each).\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO #3:</strong> In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SocialMediaRunner</code> class:\r\n- Call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">createPost()</code> method for some users.\r\n- Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getPublicPosts()</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getHiddenPosts()</code> to print the posts.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">markPost()</code> method is <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">private</code> and should only be called inside the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">SocialMedia</code> class.\r\n</div>\r\n",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
